5: So this is all that's left of them?
8:
That's right. Your assistance in this
matter was greatly appreciated.
Though...
11:
I'm not sure what to make of her
helping us.
15:
It's... complicated. Don't worry about
her.
19:
I must say, Alk, your demeanor
strikes me as... different from before.
24:
Is this really the time for such trivial
chatter?
34:
More of them?!
To arms, men! Quickly!
39: Down, you mutts. This is my prey.
42:
How about it? Let's dance—just the
two of us.
47:
Bah. Fine. I see how it is.
Listen, Alk—and you too, wolf man.
49:
Change of plans. I've found
something worth doing on this
world. I think I'll hang around a while
longer.
53:
Understood. I'll try to find us lodgings
for the night, then.
58:
You've... certainly got your hands full
with her, don't you.
62:
You can say that again. Sorry for the
trouble...
66:
They said he was hiding out
somewhere in this area, but I haven't
seen anything so far.
69:
...You're really hung up on this guy,
huh? It's kind of weird.
73:
All those mindless errands you keep
sending me on afford me little time
to train. At this rate, I'll grow rusty.
77:
You know, up until now, I've been the
one doing all those "mindless
errands."
81:
Because that's the type of contract
you've entered into. I did warn you
before—that is not the path of a true
warrior.
100: Did you hit your head or something?
102:
I thought I was your target? Why are
you wasting your time fighting the
boy?
110:
Get out of the way, Shuilong! I need
to kill that brat! Then, finally...
119:
Can you just back up a moment
there? I'm not following.
122:
You want to kill me... to get to
Shuilong? Why, exactly?
125:
Isn't it obvious? Because you're
rubbing it in my face how close the
two of you are! I won't let you have
her!
129:
What?! H-have her?! You seriously
think I want to—
133:
What are you two babbling on
about? Are you going to fight or not?
137:
I, um, I think he wants to make a
contract with you. So to speak.
141:
That's right! Fight with me one more
time...
142:
And if I win... We'll sign a contract—in
holy matrimony!
145:
I see... Just another mutt looking to
pass down his genetic material.
147:
Nothing surprising there. You
wouldn't be the first to try. They
never did manage to hold my
attention for long, though.
151:
But I... I'm different! It's not really
something I like to say a lot but...
160:
Forget it. My patience is reaching its
limits.
175:
Now this is what I was looking for.
You fight like she does—that mad
dog.
179:
Show me, then! Show me what
you're really capable of.
185:
Hm. Shoddy craftsmanship on these
things. No matter, back to the fight—
188:
Y-your ears... Fell off?! What is the
meaning of this?!
190:
What do you mean? They're
obviously fake.
196:
You TRICKED ME! You lying, deceitful
wench!
198:
Hahaha! This just gets better and
better!
204:
How long can you last, I wonder?
How far are you willing to go?
212:
Gah... My life...
For the furry-eared!
216:
Consider me impressed... But not
terribly so—you've reached your
limits, after all.
219:
It does boggle the mind, though—to
think that a pair of animal ears exert
such enormous influence over
people's hearts...
221:
I must exploit this power to my
advantage.
